			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I wrote a function in the next version of Helpbot where you can put in a time and get a pop-up window which shows you that time in all the timezones, but my codes not working yet, and the list of 40 time zones is messy and hard to find what you are really looking for.
<br />

<br />
So, I want to ask all of you:  how should it work and look?
<br />

<br />
This is the basic way it works now:
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis hh:mm TTT 
<br />
where hh = hour in military time
<br />
where mm = minutes
<br />
where TTT = time zone code, like UTC or EST or BST
<br />

<br />
but I was thinking it needs to be able to handle all the varying ways people will want to use it, like
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:00AM UTC
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:00 AM UTC
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:AM UTC
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; when is 11:AM UTC
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11 UTC
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:00AM
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:00 AM
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11:AM 
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; when is 11:AM 
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 11 
<br />

<br />
also, it would be nice if there was a way to tell the bot two TTT's and get a much smaller answer, like maybe
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 12:17PM UTC PST
<br />

<br />
also, the bot should reply with an aditional "that's in 3 hours 27 mintutes"
<br />

<br />
also, poeple may want to do 
<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis now
<br />
and get a list of the current time in all time zones
<br />

<br />

<br />
can anyone think of a better way to invent this function, or other ways it ought to work?<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"> </span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
