			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">with the nightmare of all the time zones and all the daylight savings times, I had a brain fart today:
<br />

<br />
the best way, since /tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis    will mostlikely be for guildies only, would be to manually set a few timezones, and have conversions for only those zones
<br />

<br />

<br />
something like maybe this:
<br />

<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; add timezone +4 New York
<br />
the bot would add that as one of it's time zones it knows about
<br />
and you would manually change it when daylight savings starts and ends
<br />

<br />

<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; remove timezone New York
<br />
if you want to clean up the list of timezones
<br />

<br />

<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis 4:23PM New York
<br />
will show all the timezones that he bot knows about where New York is set to 4:23PM
<br />

<br />

<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; whenis now
<br />
shows all timezones with the current time
<br />

<br />
any others?<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"> </span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
