				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">quoting Beaker: /tell &lt;bot&gt; add timezone +4 New York 
<br />
the bot would add that as one of it's time zones it knows about 
<br />
and you would manually change it when daylight savings starts and ends/quote
<br />

<br />

<br />
Maybe also a:
<br />

<br />
/tell &lt;bot&gt; add personal +2 Oslo.
<br />

<br />
Will make the bot always respond to the nick who set that time and only that person.
<br />

<br />
So if i did then /tell &lt;bot&gt; time
<br />

<br />
*bot checks my nick, finds "Amona" in a timezone-list, sees its +2GMT and that the title it should spit out to me is "Oslo" and responds:*
<br />

<br />
[bot] Hi Amona, the time is now 20.00 in Oslo (6 PM GMT).
<br />

<br />
Just a thought.
<br />

